Create an Apple Messages for Business Channel in Service Cloud

Create a Messaging channel to let your support team help customers using Apple Messages for Business. Customers message your company from the Apple Messages app, and agents reply from the Service Console.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience. View required editions
This article applies to: Enhanced Apple Messages for Business channels

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up Messaging: Configure Messaging
To authorize Apple Messages for Business: Customize Application AND Manage Auth. Providers
To view Apple Messages for Business channels: View Setup and Configuration
To create Apple Messages for Business channels: System Administrator AND Configure Messaging OR Configure Messaging AND Customize Application AND Manage Auth. Providers AND View Setup and Configuration AND Modify All Data

In Setup, navigate to the Messaging Settings page.
Click New Channel, select Apple Messages for Business, and click Go to Apple Business Register.
Log in and select Messages for Business Accounts.
Create a Messages for Business account or update an existing one.
To test your channel in a sandbox, create a separate Apple Messages for Business account just for testing.

Complete or update your account details.
Review and accept the Messages for Business policies.
Enter your details in the Account Applicant section.
Select the commercial account.
Provide your company’s contact information and location details.
Set the messaging response time and hours.

Wait for Apple to approve your account changes, which can take up to a day. When approved, click Test your messaging service provider connection and Connect.
Click Install channel and log in to Salesforce.
Verify your channel name and Messages for Business Account ID. Optionally, customize the channel name.
Complete the flow. You can now find your channel on the Messaging Settings page.

Update your channel’s auto-responses and connect your Omni-Channel routing flow.
On the Messaging Settings page, click Edit and connect your channel to an Omni-Channel flow or queue.
In the Automated Responses section, enter consent keywords and responses and auto-responses, and click Save.
Optionally, customize the agent and customer experience for your Apple Messages for Business channel with messaging components.

Send your channel through the Apple Experience Review process. After this process, customers can start contacting you in Apple Messages for Business.

Considerations for Apple Messages for Business in Service Cloud
With an Apple Messages for Business channel, you can help customers using Apple’s native Messages app.
